	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />My first attempt at sound on PowerPak: <a href="http://home.comcast.net/~olimar/NES/powerpak_loopy.zip" class="postlink">VRC6 mapper</a>
<br />For audio out, I just stuck a resistor from pin 3 to pin 9 of the EXP port. Around 50kohm seems ok, though maybe you'd prefer using a pot instead. Previous posts about audio mods suggested sticking some caps in there too, but it sounds fine to me without any. <span style="font-size: 75%; line-height: normal">*shrug*</span>

		

